==English==

===Etymology===
From French ''[[cacophonie]]'', from Greek [[κακοφωνία]], from [[κακός]] ‘bad’ + [[φωνή]] ‘sound’.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/kəˈkɒfəni/}} ''(UK)''
*{{audio|en-us-cacophony.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|cacophon|ies}}

# A mix of [[discordant]] [[sound]]s; [[dissonance]]

